						<summary>

						<p>Slab on the threshold at the entrance into the second <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in the Mādhavasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 16th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It records the obeisance of Pāpa Timmarāju and some individuals to god Mādhavarāya by offering a garland <hi rend="italic">(tōmāla).</hi></p>						

						</summary>
